<i># My soul enslave</i>

01:18:37.298 --> 01:18:40.215
<i># Break now</i>

01:18:40.384 --> 01:18:46.257
<i># The tyrant's chain</i>

01:18:46.432 --> 01:18:50.382
<i># O save me</i>

01:18:50.561 --> 01:18:55.188
<i># Whom Thou camst</i>

01:18:55.358 --> 01:18:58.727
<i># To save</i>

01:18:58.903 --> 01:19:01.572
<i># Nor bleed</i>

01:19:01.739 --> 01:19:04.859
<i># Nor die</i>

01:19:05.034 --> 01:19:09.661
<i># In vain #</i>

01:19:16.671 --> 01:19:21.498
The subject of my address to
you this evening is adversity.

01:19:21.676 --> 01:19:24.879
<i>The average life, yours and mine,</i>

01:19:25.054 --> 01:19:27.806
<i>is often harassed and perplexed</i>

01:19:27.974 --> 01:19:30.844
<i>by disappointments and by cruelties</i>

01:19:31.018 --> 01:19:33.426
<i>beyond our control.</i>

01:19:33.604 --> 01:19:38.350
<i>Now, strangely enough, it is often
these things beyond our control...</i>

01:19:38.526 --> 01:19:40.851
<i>That's Buchanan's number.</i>

01:19:41.028 --> 01:19:45.026
Go out, call him up, tell him to
surround this place with police.

01:19:45.199 --> 01:19:49.363
- What if he asks me
- - Tell him anything.

01:19:49.537 --> 01:19:53.451
This is the time. I'm sure
Hank's round here someplace.

01:19:55.334 --> 01:19:59.996
- But I don't want to leave you.
- I don't know how else to do it, honey.

01:20:00.172 --> 01:20:02.628
You go on now.

01:20:03.926 --> 01:20:05.718
<i>...our own goodness,</i>

01:20:05.887 --> 01:20:09.386
<i>and therefore the goodness of all mankind.</i>

01:20:17.815 --> 01:20:20.816
<i>Few of us pause</i>

01:20:20.985 --> 01:20:24.021
to consider how life's
adversities work in our behalf

01:20:24.197 --> 01:20:26.734
to make better men and women of us.

01:20:26.908 --> 01:20:29.992
But I think we should pause, and pause now,

01:20:30.161 --> 01:20:34.490
to do a little stocktaking, to
look into our own hearts and lives

01:20:34.665 --> 01:20:37.785
and see what we find there.

01:20:39.045 --> 01:20:41.832
Therefore, instead of continuing the service,

01:20:42.006 --> 01:20:44.923
I think we should all return to our homes

01:20:45.092 --> 01:20:49.589
<i>for private meditation, remembering
how little we have to complain of</i>

01:20:49.764 --> 01:20:52.433
<i>and how much to be grateful for.</i>

01:20:52.600 --> 01:20:56.514
Next week, I shall discuss
the fruits of our meditations.

01:20:56.687 --> 01:21:00.555
Until then, my blessing upon
each and every one of you.

01:22:07.174 --> 01:22:09.547
This is a pleasant surprise, Doctor.

01:22:09.719 --> 01:22:11.842
Where's my boy, Drayton?

01:22:12.013 --> 01:22:13.756
He's upstairs.

01:22:13.931 --> 01:22:17.016
You've come just in time to
help my wife with his food.

01:22:17.185 --> 01:22:20.435
It seems Hank doesn't care
for our English cooking.

01:22:20.605 --> 01:22:22.396
What do you want?

01:22:22.565 --> 01:22:25.649
I'll give you money, keep my
mouth shut. All I want's my boy.

01:22:25.818 --> 01:22:30.895
And what about your wife? Did she go
outside just to get some fresh air?

01:22:31.073 --> 01:22:33.280
Tell me what you want. I'll do anything.

01:22:33.451 --> 01:22:37.283
All right. You'll see
your boy. All in good time.

01:22:37.455 --> 01:22:40.824
Hank! Hank McKenna!

01:22:42.168 --> 01:22:43.710
<i>Daddy?</i>

01:22:43.878 --> 01:22:47.128
<i>Daddy! I'm here, Daddy!</i>

01:22:47.298 --> 01:22:49.421
<i>I'm here!</i>

01:23:04.774 --> 01:23:07.016
My husband's there now, watching them.

01:23:07.193 --> 01:23:10.229
He sent me to call you so you could
do something before they get away.

01:23:10.404 --> 01:23:12.231
It isn't as easy as all that.

01:23:12.406 --> 01:23:17.282
My husband is in that chapel
waiting for me to bring help.

01:23:17.453 --> 01:23:21.747
May I speak to Mr Buchanan? He
told me to call him if I needed him.

01:23:21.916 --> 01:23:24.786
I'm awfully sorry. I can't
get in touch with him.

01:23:24.961 --> 01:23:27.962
He's at an important diplomatic
affair at the Albert Hall.

01:23:28.130 --> 01:23:30.289
Then call him there! Please call him.

01:23:30.466 --> 01:23:33.004
He's on his way. I don't know how -

01:23:33.177 --> 01:23:36.214
Mr Woburn, it isn't a matter of
days, it's a matter of minutes.

01:23:36.389 --> 01:23:39.639
Now, you've got to send
the police right away!

01:23:39.809 --> 01:23:43.427
- Or do I have to go to Albert Hall myself?
-  That won't be necessary.

01:23:43.604 --> 01:23:46.439
I'll have the chapel put
under immediate observation.

01:23:46.607 --> 01:23:50.023
By the time you get back, a
police car should be there.

01:23:50.194 --> 01:23:53.065
Tell your husband to come out
and let the police take over.

01:23:53.239 --> 01:23:56.156
Woburn, Special Branch. Hold
on. I must ring off, Mrs McKenna.

01:23:56.325 --> 01:23:59.362
Please believe me. I'll
have everything laid on.

01:24:30.401 --> 01:24:32.394
There's nobody there.

01:24:32.570 --> 01:24:35.322
- Are you Mrs McKenna?
- Yes. There's something wrong, officer.

01:24:35.489 --> 01:24:37.648
That place was full of people a few
minutes ago and now there's no-one.

01:24:37.825 --> 01:24:41.324
We are to keep it under observation
until the Scotland Yard car arrives.

01:24:41.495 --> 01:24:44.496
But my husband is in there.
There were 30 or 40 people -

01:24:44.665 --> 01:24:47.500
- When was this?
- No more than five minutes ago.

01:24:47.668 --> 01:24:50.835
- Hm, let's take a look.
- I've tried the door. It's locked.

01:24:51.005 --> 01:24:52.962
We'll have to force it open.

01:24:53.132 --> 01:24:55.421
I'm sorry, madam. We can't break in.

01:24:55.593 --> 01:24:58.594
- Requires a search warrant.
- Well, can't we get one?

01:24:58.763 --> 01:25:02.511
That all takes time. We'll
have a look around, shall we?

01:25:02.683 --> 01:25:05.601
Matthews, take the other end.

01:25:31.546 --> 01:25:35.626
<i>- There's no-one there. - Are you
certain this place was just full?</i>

01:25:35.800 --> 01:25:39.418
Of course I'm certain. I was
there myself with my husband.

01:25:39.595 --> 01:25:42.845
He sent me out to call Scotland Yard.

01:25:44.475 --> 01:25:47.476
I'm afraid it's much too
complicated to explain why.

01:25:47.645 --> 01:25:51.228
We'll just have to sit tight and
wait for the car from The Yard.

01:25:57.780 --> 01:26:00.900
- There's no sign of life.
- Report back here.

01:26:01.075 --> 01:26:04.444
Very good, sir. Walden, you stand by
and wait for the car from The Yard.

01:26:04.620 --> 01:26:06.613
- That's all, Matthews.
- You're not leaving?

01:26:06.789 --> 01:26:10.158
Orders, madam. Can we
give you a lift somewhere?

01:26:10.334 --> 01:26:13.584
- Take me to Albert Hall, please.
- The Albert Hall's off our beat.

01:26:13.754 --> 01:26:17.752
Suppose we drop you off
at the nearest taxi rank?

01:27:35.753 --> 01:27:37.829
Wait here.

01:27:43.719 --> 01:27:47.219
- They're here.
- Wait till I clear the kitchen.

01:27:57.817 --> 01:28:01.067
Everybody out! Into the
corridor. Five minutes.

01:28:01.237 --> 01:28:03.064
Come on!

01:28:03.239 --> 01:28:06.074
Do as he tells you. Come
on. It'll only take a minute.

01:28:06.242 --> 01:28:08.911
Come on. All of you, out.

01:28:27.305 --> 01:28:29.381
All right. This way.

01:28:31.976 --> 01:28:34.645
Always something funny
going on at this embassy.

01:28:34.812 --> 01:28:38.430
- Bringing people in in secret.
- Give me the Swiss embassy anytime.

01:28:38.608 --> 01:28:40.766
There's neutrality for you.

01:30:01.566 --> 01:30:03.724
Please, may I see the manager?

01:30:03.901 --> 01:30:06.571
I'm sorry, madam. The
manager's on duty in the lobby.

01:30:06.737 --> 01:30:10.023
- So is his assistant.
- I must speak with them.

01:30:10.199 --> 01:30:12.821
Over there somewhere.

01:30:36.100 --> 01:30:39.184
You have a very nice little boy, madam.

01:30:39.353 --> 01:30:43.268
<i>His safety will depend upon you tonight.</i>

01:30:43.441 --> 01:30:46.395
Where is he? Where is he?

01:30:58.206 --> 01:31:00.245
Good evening.

01:31:00.416 --> 01:31:03.287
<i>- Is that the prime minister?
- No, the ambassador.</i>

01:31:03.461 --> 01:31:06.415
<i>His prime minister's the
one with the bald head.</i>

01:31:31.864 --> 01:31:36.407
- Your ticket, madam?
- I'm sorry. I'm looking for someone.

