What happened?

01:41:28.544 --> 01:41:31.913
I saw the gun. He was pointing
it at the Prime Minister.

01:41:32.089 --> 01:41:34.877
He was going to kill him, and
I realised I had to scream.

01:41:48.606 --> 01:41:52.817
- Then he didn't kill him?
- Your wife saved him.

01:41:54.570 --> 01:41:56.397
Oh, there they are.

01:41:56.572 --> 01:41:59.775
Please come over and let
the prime minister thank you.

01:41:59.951 --> 01:42:03.450
It won't take very long.
Would you come along?

01:42:09.627 --> 01:42:11.750
Oh, yes.

01:42:11.921 --> 01:42:14.957
Yes. Prime Minister, this is the young lady.

01:42:15.132 --> 01:42:17.670
Dear lady, I'm forever in your debt.

01:42:17.843 --> 01:42:19.753
<i>This is her husband.</i>

01:42:19.929 --> 01:42:22.716
I trust you'll permit me
to wait upon you tomorrow

01:42:22.890 --> 01:42:26.805
and to express to you
the depth of my gratitude.

01:42:26.978 --> 01:42:31.805
- It wasn't - - But it
was, my dear lady. It was.

01:42:31.983 --> 01:42:35.399
Will you excuse us.

01:42:35.570 --> 01:42:37.609
Excuse me, but I have to go.

01:42:45.913 --> 01:42:48.831
I think Mr Buchanan would
like a word with you.

01:42:54.672 --> 01:42:56.665
Where's our boy? Where's Hank?

01:42:56.841 --> 01:43:00.174
We can talk if you'll come in here.

01:43:02.763 --> 01:43:04.388
So you both knew the
time and place all along.

01:43:04.557 --> 01:43:05.932
Don't be a fool.

01:43:06.100 --> 01:43:08.342
An odd coincidence, both
of you turning up here.

01:43:08.519 --> 01:43:11.354
It's a pity you didn't contact your
assistant. He told us you were here.

01:43:11.522 --> 01:43:14.607
- I beg your pardon?
- We need that help you offered.

01:43:17.153 --> 01:43:19.478
Sir, we've questioned the woman.

01:43:19.655 --> 01:43:22.146
Said she bought a ticket which
happened to place her in the box

01:43:22.325 --> 01:43:24.317
with the man who did the shooting.

01:43:24.493 --> 01:43:27.067
- If she knows anything, she won't say.
- I'll see her later.

01:43:27.246 --> 01:43:30.081
- Very good, sir.
- Please tell me everything, now.

01:43:30.249 --> 01:43:34.199
Everything. There's still
plenty of room for hope.

01:43:42.845 --> 01:43:45.052
His Excellency will see you now.

01:44:08.871 --> 01:44:10.698
And that's that, I suppose.

01:44:10.873 --> 01:44:12.913
Yes. All right.

01:44:17.088 --> 01:44:21.216
Excuse me, sir. I have
a lot to explain to you.

01:44:21.384 --> 01:44:23.922
<i>Something very unusual has happened.</i>

01:44:25.596 --> 01:44:28.383
I also have to have the
money to pay the marksman.

01:44:28.558 --> 01:44:30.799
Wouldn't that be superfluous,

01:44:30.977 --> 01:44:33.550
considering... that he's dead?

01:44:40.903 --> 01:44:44.853
His aim wasn't quite as
good as you led me to expect.

01:44:45.032 --> 01:44:48.532
The target merely received a
slight flesh wound in the arm.

01:44:48.703 --> 01:44:50.909
Worse than useless.

01:44:51.080 --> 01:44:54.781
Then your French friend
panicked, made a fatal crash,

01:44:54.959 --> 01:44:57.746
landing on the floor of the Albert Hall.

01:45:01.841 --> 01:45:04.795
I don't see how you can blame me for that.

01:45:04.969 --> 01:45:07.590
He was warmly recommended
by our people in Marrakech.

01:45:07.763 --> 01:45:11.049
I'm glad that you are able to
treat the matter so lightly.

01:45:11.225 --> 01:45:13.550
I'm holding a reception here this evening.

01:45:13.728 --> 01:45:17.560
In a few moments, I have to welcome our
prime minister as my guest of honour,

01:45:17.732 --> 01:45:21.564
when I hoped and expected that he
would be totally unable to attend.

01:45:23.487 --> 01:45:27.271
- That amuses you, no doubt.
- I don't know what to say...

01:45:27.450 --> 01:45:28.730
<i>No.</i>

01:45:31.495 --> 01:45:35.327
But I do. You have muddled
everything from the start.

01:45:35.499 --> 01:45:37.991
Taking that child with you from Marrakech.

01:45:38.169 --> 01:45:41.620
Don't you realise that Americans
dislike having their children stolen?

01:45:41.797 --> 01:45:44.834
How else could I make sure
that McKenna would keep quiet?

01:45:45.009 --> 01:45:48.010
Then, to crown it all, you get cold feet

01:45:48.179 --> 01:45:52.177
and come running along here to hide,
bringing the wretched child with you.

01:45:52.350 --> 01:45:55.719
Don't you see what you've done to
the diplomatic status of this embassy?

01:45:55.895 --> 01:45:57.934
I didn't think. I only thought we could -

01:45:58.105 --> 01:46:02.851
How are you going to get the
child out of here, eh? Eh? EH?

01:46:03.027 --> 01:46:06.063
No difficulty about that, surely? The car.

01:46:06.239 --> 01:46:10.616
With plainclothes detectives
planted right 'round this building?

01:46:10.785 --> 01:46:13.536
You English intellectuals
will be the death of us all.

01:46:13.704 --> 01:46:15.662
I'll think of something. Only give me time.

01:46:15.831 --> 01:46:17.374
Time. Huh!

01:46:25.383 --> 01:46:28.633
I want the child removed from this embassy,

01:46:28.803 --> 01:46:33.631
and removed in such a way that
he won't be able to say any more

01:46:33.808 --> 01:46:35.432
where he has been tonight.

01:46:35.601 --> 01:46:37.558
Oh, no!

01:46:40.940 --> 01:46:44.143
<i>- I'll see to it.
- Drayton!</i>

01:46:44.318 --> 01:46:47.236
I trust that nothing will go wrong this time.

01:46:53.619 --> 01:46:55.826
It would be very unfortunate for you if -

01:46:58.082 --> 01:46:59.541
Yes, come in.

01:47:02.169 --> 01:47:06.119
Your Excellency, the princess
should be arriving at any moment.

01:47:18.311 --> 01:47:20.849
I recognised him. He recognised me.

01:47:21.022 --> 01:47:24.106
He tried to get away, made
a jump for it. That was all.

01:47:24.275 --> 01:47:27.062
Trying to liquidate one
of their own big shots.

01:47:27.236 --> 01:47:30.570
I wish they'd stick to their usual
custom and do it in their own country.

01:47:32.992 --> 01:47:35.068
Yes?

01:47:36.579 --> 01:47:39.152
Buchanan speaking.

01:47:41.959 --> 01:47:44.035
Right. Thank you.

01:47:44.712 --> 01:47:46.586
The Draytons are at the embassy.

01:47:46.756 --> 01:47:48.333
- The what?
- How do you know?

01:47:48.507 --> 01:47:51.793
We have ways of finding out, from the inside.

01:47:51.969 --> 01:47:55.089
If the Draytons are at the
embassy, then our boy's there too.

01:47:55.264 --> 01:47:59.511
- Probably. But we can't do anything.
- What do you mean?

01:47:59.685 --> 01:48:02.307
Every embassy in a foreign country has extra
- territorial rights.

01:48:02.480 --> 01:48:05.765
- What's that?
- It's as if the embassy is on foreign soil.

01:48:05.942 --> 01:48:09.441
So they can steal kids and
get away with it? What is this!

01:48:09.612 --> 01:48:13.147
<i>We could have the Foreign Office
serve a writ on the ambassador.</i>

01:48:13.324 --> 01:48:16.823
I'm not responsible for the
complications of international law.

01:48:16.994 --> 01:48:21.989
<i>If only we had some positive proof
that your boy really is in there.</i>

01:48:28.047 --> 01:48:31.001
Say, wh-what's the phone
number of that embassy?

01:48:31.175 --> 01:48:33.666
- You got it? - What
are you thinking of -

01:48:33.844 --> 01:48:37.011
- Let me try something.
- Grosvenor 0-1-4-4.

01:48:37.181 --> 01:48:40.135
Grosvenor
0-1-4-4, please.

01:48:40.309 --> 01:48:43.476
That fellow that got shot's
a prime minister, isn't he?

01:48:45.356 --> 01:48:49.354
<i>Hello? Hello, I'd like to speak
to the prime minister, please.</i>

01:48:49.527 --> 01:48:51.401
Yeah, yeah. No, look...

01:48:51.571 --> 01:48:54.406
Just tell him the lady that saved
his life would like to speak to him.

01:48:54.574 --> 01:48:57.195
- It's very important.
- Ben, what do I say?

01:48:57.368 --> 01:49:00.037
He wanted to visit with
us so he could thank you.

01:49:00.204 --> 01:49:02.778
Tell him you want to come
over to the embassy tonight,

01:49:02.957 --> 01:49:05.246
cos we're going to leave London tomorrow.

01:49:05.418 --> 01:49:07.494
Hello? Here you are.

01:49:07.670 --> 01:49:08.749
Hello?

01:49:08.921 --> 01:49:13.417
My dear lady, this is a charming surprise.

01:49:13.593 --> 01:49:16.380
Uh-huh.

01:49:16.554 --> 01:49:19.887
Mm-hm. Delighted. Delighted, delighted.

01:49:20.057 --> 01:49:22.727
The ambassador too would be delighted.

01:49:22.894 --> 01:49:25.431
Any friends of mine are friends of his.

01:49:29.066 --> 01:49:30.691
He said all right.

01:49:32.361 --> 01:49:34.687
- If he asks you, we're all set.
- What if they don't?

01:49:34.864 --> 01:49:37.569
Have we ever been to a party
where they didn't ask you?

01:49:37.742 --> 01:49:41.692
Now, your job is to hold
their attention, right?

01:49:45.750 --> 01:49:48.122
Good evening
- Dr and Mrs McKenna.

01:49:48.294 --> 01:49:50.619
How very nice to see you.

01:49:50.796 --> 01:49:54.248
The prime minister's waiting
for you. Come this way.

01:50:02.183 --> 01:50:04.057
Ah, madame!

01:50:04.769 --> 01:50:08.352
- Good evening, good evening.
- Good evening.

01:50:08.523 --> 01:50:12.223
This is the charming lady who
saved my life at the concert.

01:50:12.401 --> 01:50:18.072
Madam, you saved the life of the one
man who's irreplaceable in our country.

01:50:19.283 --> 01:50:22.154
<i>I hear you are the famous Jo Conway, madame?</i>

01:50:22.328 --> 01:50:25.614
<i>- Yes, I'm Jo Conway.
- Perhaps we might...</i>

01:50:25.790 --> 01:50:28.541
I'm sure my wife would be
delighted to sing for you.

01:50:28.709 --> 01:50:31.829
- Wouldn't you, dear?
- Well, it's been quite some time...

01:50:32.004 --> 01:50:33.249
I beg you, madame.

01:50:33.422 --> 01:50:37.206
<i>A tranquil coda to
conclude a dramatic evening.</i>

01:50:37.385 --> 01:50:39.923
I'm very flattered.

01:50:40.096 --> 01:50:41.923
Um, Stanis?

01:50:42.098 --> 01:50:44.553
<i>Would you put up some
chairs? And hurry up, please.</i>

01:50:44.725 --> 01:50:50.479
<i>Ladies and gentlemen, Jo Conway has
consented to sing a few songs for us.</i>

01:50:50.648 --> 01:50:56.437
<i>Darling, would you see that the
prime minister gets a good seat.</i>

01:50:56.612 --> 01:51:00.692
Would you like to come to the
piano? I do hope it's tuned.

01:51:00.867 --> 01:51:04.117
<i>- Would you not like to sit down, sir?
- Er...</i>

01:51:04.287 --> 01:51:07.952
No, thank you. I'll just stand over here.

